// Arlen app-enrollment apt hook (app-enrollment §E4).
//
// Install as /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/99arlen-enroll.
//
// apt streams the pending package changes to this hook on stdin before
// unpacking, so a package that has a curated starting profile is confined from
// its first launch rather than after someone notices it running unconfined.
//
// Pre-Install-Pkgs, not Post-Invoke: the profile must exist before the binary
// does. The hook runs as root inside apt, which is why it is the permission
// helper (the root component that owns /var/lib/arlen/permissions) rather than
// installd, a per-user session service that cannot write there.
//
// Version 3 is the stream format the parser was captured against. It always
// exits 0 - a failed enrolment must never abort a package operation, since
// leaving one package unconfined is recoverable and a broken `apt install` is
// not.
DPkg::Pre-Install-Pkgs { "/usr/lib/arlen/permission-helper --apt-hook"; };
DPkg::Tools::Options::"/usr/lib/arlen/permission-helper --apt-hook"::Version "3";

// Second stage, after dpkg has unpacked. It cannot be folded into the first:
// Pre-Install-Pkgs runs before the files exist, so the .desktop entries whose
// Exec= has to point at arlen-run are not there yet. Post-Invoke is handed no
// package list, so the first stage writes one to /var/lib/arlen for this one to
// consume. Fires on every apt run and does nothing when that list is empty.
DPkg::Post-Invoke { "/usr/lib/arlen/permission-helper --apt-post-install"; };
